    "actor_description": "My attention goes to them like it has weight. It isn't curiosity—it's pull. Something in me tightens, not with fear, but with readiness: What do you need? What can I do? I feel it physically—jaw softening, breath turning careful, hands wanting to move without being told. I don't have to like someone to recognize hurt. I just have to see it.",
    "description_text": "{actor}'s face changes first: the brow eases, the eyes narrow in focus rather than suspicion. Their posture tilts forward a fraction—an unconscious lean toward the problem. Their hands make small, restrained movements, as if they're measuring whether touch would help or harm.",
